						<summary>

						<p>This is another verse in praise of Adigēśan, Adiyamāṉ Viḍu-Kādaḻagiya Perumāḷ (of Tagaḍūr) who having swept over the country of Teṉ-Koṅgu, made himself master of the Gaṅga country. Below the inscription is engraved the figure of a parasol flanked on either side with a <hi rend="italic">chāmara</hi> (flywhisk).</p>						

						</summary>
